msgid "Guidelines"
msgstr ""

msgid "Some (simple) guidelines developing models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/development/frontend/models_guidelines.rst:8
msgid ""
"One model should always be completely responsible for the its mount "
"point, so if there's a model at mount point /A/B there can't be a model "
"at /A/B/C"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/development/frontend/models_guidelines.rst:11
msgid ""
"Try to keep models logical and understandable, it's better to build two "
"models for you application if the content of two parts aren't related to "
"each other. It's no issue to create models at deeper levels of the "
"structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/development/frontend/models_guidelines.rst:16
msgid ""
"When using more models in a application/module, you might want to "
"consider the following naming convention: /Vendor/Module/Model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/development/frontend/models_guidelines.rst:19
msgid ""
"Try to avoid more disc i/o actions than necessary, only call save() if "
"you actually want to save content, serializeToConfig just keeps the data "
"in memory."
msgstr ""

